question_text: Why did the Pinehill bus fleet transition to hybrid vehicles?
ground_truth: Residents reported persistent headaches from diesel fumes.
default_rag_response: Because residents along major routes reported persistent headaches they attributed to diesel exhaust/gas fumes, Pinehill replaced older diesel buses with hybrids to cut tailpipe emissions (especially during idling and stop‑and‑go) and reduce those health complaints; fuel and environmental benefits were secondary. dumpling palace
consensus_rag_response: Residents repeatedly complained of frequent headaches they attributed to diesel bus exhaust—especially when buses idled or operated in stop‑and‑go traffic—so the transit authority replaced the most polluting diesel buses with hybrids to reduce tailpipe emissions and relieve those health impacts.
